            <Section1 ID="Sec01028">
              <Heading>Summary</Heading>
              <Para>We used WRF meteorology as an input to a neural network to predict the hourly ground level O<Subscript>3</Subscript> for the next 3 and 24 h. Preliminary results show that the WRF model was able to provide reliable meteorological data, though with significant negative bias for air temperature estimates. ANN were reliable for short 3 h forecasts, but significantly underestimated measured O<Subscript>3</Subscript> for 24 h forecasts.</Para>
              <Para>Further steps will include improvements of WRF meteorology – preliminary results show that the MB for T2 can be decreased by changing the model configuration. ANN will be rerun with the improved meteorology, and tested for a larger number of sites. Finally, we will use the WRF-ANN approach for spatial, short term O<Subscript>3</Subscript> forecasting and compare the results with atmospheric transport model.</Para>
            </Section1>
